      public CollisionData reflect​(CollisionData incident)
      Creates a reflection of the given data about the sphere.

      REQUIRES: incident != null. EFFECTS: Creates a new data with the new location and speed to be reflected. MODIFIES: None

      Parameters:
      incident - Data of the incident vector.
      Returns:
      Returns a collision data of how it is going to be reflected.

    • reflect

      public CollisionData reflect​(CollisionData incident, Obstacle obstacle) throws java.lang.Exception
      Creates a reflection of the given data about the sphere.

      REQUIRES: incident != null, obstacle's X and Y coordinates should be inside of the gameMap. EFFECTS: Creates a new data with the new location and speed to be reflected. MODIFIES: None

      Parameters:
      incident - Data of the incident vector.
      Returns:
      Returns a collision data of how it is going to be reflected.
